notes: ee-this, che-is, aapner-our, eez-this, aapner-our, parampara che - is legacy

english: In the late 16th century, the Mughal Empire defeated Rana Pratap.
banjara: soole shaatbtheer ma, mughaleer aan rana pratap een haaraye
notes: deer-late, soole-16, shaatbtheer-century, ma-in, mughaleer-mughal's, aan-came, rana pratap een - rana pratap, haaraye - defeated

english: We followed Rana Pratap into the forests.
banjara: apan rana prathap eer laar jungleuuma chalege
notes: hum-we, apan-we, rana prathap eer-rana prathap's, laar-after/behind, jungleuuma-in forests, chalege-went

english: Then began our great migration south.
banjara: jannateez apan dhakshan bharath eer vadi dagaryaye.
notes: tho-then, aapner-our, jannateez-from then only, apan-us/we, dhakshan bharatheer -south of india's,  vadi-side, dagaryaye-came.

banjara: madhya pradesh eer malwa mai thi
notes: madhya pradesh eer-madhya pradesh's, malwa-malwa, mai thi-from inside/from it.

english: Through the Deccan region of Maharashtra.
banjara: maharastra mai eer deccan ilaka thi leethanin
notes: eevur-of, maharastra mai eer-inside maharastra, deccan ilaka-deccan region, thi-from,  leethanin-took

english: Finally settling in Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, and Telangana.
banjara: karnataka, andhra pradesh, telangana lugni nikalyaye
notes: anne-and, karnataka-karnataka, andhra pradesh-andhra pradesh, telangana-telangana, lugni-till, nikalyaye-came from there

english: Sant Sevalal's grandfather, Ramji Naik Rathod, led this migration.
banjara: sant sevalal eero dadha, Ramji Naik Rathod eer nayaki ma chalpade.
notes: ee-this, sant sevalal eero-sant sevalal's, dadha-grandfather, Ramji Naik Rathod eer-Ramji Naik Rathod's, nayaki-leadership, ma-in, chalpade-started walking/walked.
